<title>SPAIN: Peseta debt/interbank closing report.</title>
<headline>Peseta debt/interbank closing report.</headline>
<dateline>MADRID 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Spanish government bonds were sharply higher along with the peseta in late trade on Thursday, boosted after a 30 bp cut in the Bundesbank's repo rate.</p>
<p>Analysts said the Buba's unexpectedly aggressive move increased the margin for the Spanish central bank to cut rates, but did not necessarily affect the timing.</p>
<p>Some expect no Spanish repo cut until at least after August inflation data, but most are consider news on the 1997 budget will condition the timing of the next easing.</p>
<p>&quot;We still think the Bank of Spain will link a rate cut to the budget,&quot; said Antonio Villarroya, analyst at Merrill Lynch.</p>
</text>
